Brazilian capital city, Brasilia, is the seat of government and located in the central part of the country. It was built in the 1960s under the presidency of Juscelino Kubitschek. The construction of Brasilia was a major modernization and urbanization project of the time. The capital city has the typical look of an international modernist architecture with five large white domes and is home to over 200,000 people.
